" to compensate for voltage loss on long cabling. Without that, it is not "
"possible to properly switch the polarization."
msgstr ""
"Some DVB 设备 have an optional ioctl that allows changing between normal "
"voltage for 高频头 (13V/18V) to a higher voltage 模式 (usually, 14V/19V), meant "
"to compensate for voltage loss on long cabling. Without that, it is not "
"possible to properly switch the polarization."

